# Frontend Environment Configuration

## Development Environment (.env.development)

```
REACT_APP_API_URL=http://localhost:8080/api
REACT_APP_ENV=development
```

## Production Environment (.env.production)

```
REACT_APP_API_URL=https://api.timeoutairline.com/api
REACT_APP_ENV=production
```

## How to Use

1. Create a `.env` file in the root of the `frontend` directory (next to package.json)
2. Copy the appropriate configuration from above based on your environment
3. The application will automatically use these variables

## Available Environment Variables

- `REACT_APP_API_URL` - Backend API base URL
- `REACT_APP_ENV` - Environment name (development/production)

## Updating API Endpoint

If you need to change the API endpoint:

1. Edit `.env` file
2. Change `REACT_APP_API_URL` value
3. Restart the development server

For example, if backend runs on port 3001:
```
REACT_APP_API_URL=http://localhost:3001/api
```

## Important Notes

- All custom environment variables must start with `REACT_APP_`
- Restart the development server after changing `.env` file
- `.env` files should NOT be committed to version control
- Use `.env.example` for documentation purposes

